<br>
It gets a little disorienting, but I believe that as you enter the room below, the hand is above and behind you. I may be very wrong about that though (adrenaline and all that), but I can definitely say that the Hand did not aggro on me, even though I had to surface several times right in front of him. The hard part is simply not stepping out of the water as you bob up and down. The safest course is simply waiting for the hand room to be camped, but that wasn't a satisfactory uption on Sullon <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Regardless of campedness, if you stick to the left wall in the bat room and the right wall as you run past the big skellies (both of which see through invis vs undead) they should not agro on you. Then jump down to the left when you get to the bridge (you will take a few damage here, but this gets you onto the part of the www.eqatlas.com map that has all the straight lines) The very small and hard to see box with an 'x' in it on that same map is a pit that you can jump over, it is right after something that looked sort of like a bed of coals. If you fall down the pit, just climb up the ladder, and you will be just past the hand room hallway if memory serves. NOTE: there are two passages from the &quot;bedroom&quot; to the &quot;bat&quot; room, take the left one or else...<br>
