Big story ahead... :-)<br>
<br>
I managed to finally get my Staff of the Wheel last night. And well pleased I am too - 204 int and looking good :-)<br>
<br>
As for the rod in Lower Guk... well... can you say &quot;awkward&quot;? :-)<br>
<br>
I decided to make myself a little stooge rogue so that I could have a poke around in there undetected... got my brother to port him over to S.Ro and legged it into Guk. Sneak/hide took a couple of times to stick but then I snuck all the way through to the hand room (aside - you don't *have* to drop down the pit near the room - the trap is easily avoided).<br>
<br>
It's an odd room alright. When you enter the room the ledge with the hand and &quot;a-n-other-spawn&quot; is above your head. If you go to the back wall and swim up there you're going to be as far away from the ledge as you get.<br>
<br>
My rogue spent at least 30 minutes in there watching things. One thing I found was that, when he first surfaced, the hand was waaay back at the rear of the ledge, a ghoul wizard was in the middle of the ledge and the rod was right at the front next to the waterline.<br>
<br>
Just out of interest, he grabbed the rod that was there, destroyed it, and then got out of the water for a look around.<br>
<br>
I waited for ages for the rod to respawn and didnt' see it. Then finally I noticed that the rod had respawned in a different place. There are at least five different spawn spots for it on that ledge. Some at the front, some right at the back.<br>
<br>
I can see that, if you were *really* lucky and the hand was right at the back of the ledge and the rod had spawned right at the front of the ledge and you still had Invis to Undead on then you *might* be able to grab it from in the water.<br>
<br>
However, after my recon mission with the rogue I decided that I knew where I was going and what I was doing so I collared a Cleric at the Upper Guk zone.<br>
<br>
He duelled me to death to make me naked and then provided Invis to Undead for me.<br>
<br>
I ran right to the hand room and, ignoring my initial decision to camp there and bring my rogue back on to check the status above the water, I swam up at the furthest point away from the hand.<br>
<br>
When I turned around to look at the ledge, the hand was swimming towards me and the wizard was firing up a spell. Doh!<br>
<br>
I swam for the ledge, jumped up, glanced at the places I knew the rod spawned, located it, looted it, stuck it in my inventory, jumped back in the water and then promptly forgot to even try gating. I died.<br>
<br>
I then decided that my level 2 rogue could help me out. I logged him on (he's still there, camped in the hand room!) and found my corpse sitting on the floor under the water. Hooray! A body with the rod on it --- now to get it out of there...<br>
<br>
Good old rogue dragged that body around for ages before finally admitting defeat and /ooc'ing &quot;How do I get off the level with the hand room&quot;?<br>
<br>
Many replies of &quot;you're screwed dude&quot; convinced me that there was no way back up to the zone line. Doh!<br>
<br>
I decided to leave my body right next to the place you drop off, hoping that with Invis to Undead my Wizard could get there and /corpse the body up top.<br>
<br>
Things became complicated when my brother's level-60 Druid and my friend's level 57 warrior and 58 cleric turned up to &quot;help&quot;. Invising us, the druid and I ran down to get my body. It had disappeared. The cleric at the zone line said something about my body being up there. Confused we dallied a little too long and my Invis to Undead dropped. Of course, I was fully kitted out at this point, having looted my main corpse.<br>
<br>
So now I had two bodies in Lower Guk. One with a rod for the quest and another with all my equipment on it.<br>
<br>
Doh!<br>
<br>
So, me, level 60 druid, level 57 warrior and level 58 cleric all hump down to the hand level again. I get a handy rez from the cleric's epic rez-stick and loot my main corpse. Phew - there's a relief.<br>
<br>
We spend a while hunting for my rod corpse to no avail. I gate back to Upper Guk and log my rogue on to retrace his steps to see where the body might be. Just before I camp they tell me that the warrior can target my corpse near where I left it but cannot drag it. They then go back to the zone and find that my body is also there - poking through the wall - and also cannot drag it (even though they were consented).<br>
<br>
Doh! My corpse is bugged!<br>
<br>
One &quot;wait for a reply to a /petition&quot; later and a GM puts my body nicely on the floor at the zone line. One rez later and I'm back together, most of my xp intact and the rod in my hands! Whoot!<br>
<br>
So, lessons to be learned...<br>
<br>
1) The hand may or may not aggro you when you surface - it depends on where he is on the ledge. I'm basing the &quot;not aggro&quot; on reports from others that he didn't aggro them.<br>
<br>
2) The rod does not spawn in exactly the same spot each time. Expect to have a quick hunt for it around the ledge. The five spots I saw were rear left, rear right (rear being right at the back), front left, front right and front centre.<br>
<br>
3) Follow the tried-and-true method of dying in the water, going back, looting your body under the water then gating out. You can't really put the corpse anywhere &quot;safer&quot; than the spot it drops from the water.<br>
<br>
4) While in the hand room my rogue saw undead frogloks come as far as the doorway of the room. Beware of this. If you are against the rear wall of the room (below the water) then they won't aggro but if you're any further forward towards the door I can imagine problems if ItU drops.<br>
<br>
<br>
